content.text:
The issue was caused by `ImportOrderingRule` incorrectly adding a blank line at the beginning of the import list if the `ij_kotlin_imports_layout` configuration had a `|` (blank line symbol) before the group matching the first import, even if all preceding groups in the layout were empty. This resulted in extra blank lines between the package declaration and the first import.

I have fixed this by ensuring that blank lines are only inserted between two imports. The logic now skips checking for blank lines when processing the first import in the list (`prev == null`).

### Changes made:
- Modified `ktlint-ruleset-standard/src/main/kotlin/com/pinterest/ktlint/ruleset/standard/rules/ImportOrderingRule.kt` to only check for and insert blank lines when there is a previous import to compare with.
- Added a reproduction test case in `ktlint-ruleset-standard/src/test/kotlin/com/pinterest/ktlint/ruleset/standard/rules/importordering/ImportOrderingRuleIssueReproTest.kt` to verify the fix and prevent regressions.

Verified that the new test passes and all existing import ordering tests continue to pass.

```kotlin
// ktlint-ruleset-standard/src/main/kotlin/com/pinterest/ktlint/ruleset/standard/rules/ImportOrderingRule.kt

// ... around line 76 ...
                val sortedImportsWithSpaces = mutableListOf<ASTNode>()
                sortedImports.fold(null as ASTNode?) { prev, current ->
                    val index2 = importSorter.findImportIndex((current.psi as KtImportDirective).importPath!!)
                    if (prev != null) {
                        val index1 = importSorter.findImportIndex((prev.psi as KtImportDirective).importPath!!)

                        var hasBlankLines = false
                        for (i in (index1 + 1) until index2) {
                            if (importSorter.patterns[i] == PatternEntry.BLANK_LINE_ENTRY) {
                                hasBlankLines = true
                                break
                            }
                        }
                        if (hasBlankLines) {
                            sortedImportsWithSpaces += PsiWhiteSpaceImpl("\n\n")
                        }
                    }
                    sortedImportsWithSpaces += current

                    return@fold current
                }
```

The fix ensures that the `|` symbol in the imports layout only triggers a blank line between non-empty groups.

